Hewlett-Packard Co And Its NGEN Alliance Partners, Including International Business Machines Corp's IBM Global Business Services Federal Wins U.S. Department of Navy's NGEN Contract
Thursday, 27 Jun 2013 07:28pm EDT
Hewlett-Packard Co's Enterprise Services and its NGEN Alliance Partners, AT&T Government Solutions, Inc., International Business Machines Corp's IBM Global Business Services Federal, Lockheed Martin Services, Inc. and Northrop Grumman Systems Corp., announced they have been awarded the U.S. Department of the Navy's (DON) Next Generation Enterprise Network (NGEN) contract. Valued at approximately $3.45 billion over five years if all options are exercised, the contract covers a broad range of information technology (IT) services and support for more than 800,000 Sailors, Marines and civilians in the continental United States, Hawaii and Japan. According to the Navy, the initial $321,689,010 indefinite-delivery/indefinite-quantity (IDIQ), firm-fixed award fee contract for NGEN will continue through June 2018 if all options are exercised.Â 
